<h1>Problem 418 - 2019 China TST Test 1, P6 of 6</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 9</h2>
<p>Let \(k\) be a positive real. \(A\) and \(B\) play the following game: at the start, there are \(80\) zeroes arranged around a circle. Each turn, \(A\) increases some of these \(80\) numbers, such that the total sum added is 1. Next, \(B\) selects the ten consecutive numbers with the largest sum, and reduces them all to \(0.\) \(A\) then wins the game if she can ensure that at least one of the numbers is \(\geq k\) at some point in time.
<br><br>
Determine all \(k\) such that \(A\) can always win the game.</p>
